    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="917"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d917">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">562.8F2/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-24T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 24, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>195. For Johnson. Embassy’s 300, May 21, 6.00 p.m. To raise the minimum length of
                    immature blue whales to 75 feet will necessitate amending the Whaling Act which
                    stipulates under Section 4 the minimum length of blue whales as 60 feet. The
                    limitation of the number of killer boats accompanying each factory and the
                    restriction of the daily catch to the amount that can be converted within 24
                    hours can be accomplished by modifying the regulations authorized under Section
                    5 and issued jointly by the Secretary of Commerce and the Secretary of the
                        Treasury<note n="7" xml:id="d917fn7">
                        <hi rend="italic">Federal Register</hi>, October 17, 1936, p. 1616.</note>
                    for the purpose of carrying out the objectives of the Convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
